AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet wonderful Willow a Terrier mix born around April 2017. Willow is a goofy, playful, sweet girl that will surely bring lots of love and smiles to a family. She is good with kids, dogs and even cats. She walks well on leash and is house and crate trained. Willow was recently rescued from an area shelter and is adjusting well in her foster home. She is such a funny girl and loves to bury herself under blankets to take nap or just to play. She loves to snuggle and be around her family. She is learning basic commands and doing well. She is a smart girl that is treat motivated. Willow would be best suited in a home with a fenced in yard where she can run and play. She is current on vaccines, microchipped, will be spayed and around 35lbs. It's Valentine's week! But some of our pets enjoy the "single" life - they want to be the only pet in the household! They want a couple great friends to hang out with (you & your family), but no other furry companions. So in their "Single & Lovin' It" spirit, this Valentine's week you can adopt a single pet for $0 adoption fee!
Everything is still included. Talk about an inexpensive date!

Smiley senior Yucon is a super sweet and affectionate gentleman. At 10 years of age, he has playful tendencies and bursts of energy that prove age is just a number! This happy meatball is 74 pounds but thinks he is a lap dog and likes to climb onto your lap for smooches if you give him the chance. 😙 He is calm and easygoing, already knows how to sit and walks well on leash. Talk about a silver fox! Yucon has been waiting at the shelter since December 2, 2017 and is so ready to find a home of his own. All of our dogs deserve a home with a soft warm bed to call their own, but this is especially true for seniors! Come in to meet dear Mr. Yucon today!
Yucon is *Blue/Medically Alerted for geriatric, worn teeth*. SHARE to help his special family find him!
Yucon 🤠💘 #A1744352
